TITLE: Wishes for Relative
INSIDEVERSE:
Cover Verse:

Know what
I'm wishing
for Christmas
this year.
Stephanie?

Inside Verse:

...that everyone
in the whole wide world
could have a relative
as nice as you!

Merry Christmas
from My Heart to Yours

TITLE: Forever Friend
INSIDEVERSE:
Cover Verse:

Merry Christmas
to Michelle.
My "Forever Friend"

Inside Verse:

You're not just
a friend for today —
you're a friend for life.
and that's why
I'm wishing you
a Christmas filled with
enough "merry"
to last a lifetime!

TITLE: To a Dear Relative
INSIDEVERSE:
Cover Verse:

To a Dear Relative
with Love from Richard

Inside Verse:

For all the thoughtful
things you've done
and all the happiness
you've given.
this card comes
with a heart full of gratitude
and wishes for a
very merry Christmas.

Merry Christmas. John.
and Happy New Year

TITLE: Magic of Friends
INSIDEVERSE:
Cover Verse:

Jennifer.
it's not the trees or tinsel
that make the season special...

Inside Verse:

It's gentle friends like you
who bring a certain sparkle
to the holidays.
For in the warmth
of your bright spirit.
the magic of Christmas
is something real and true!

MERRY CHRISTMAS

TITLE: Christmas Wishes
INSIDEVERSE:
Cover Verse:

For the Peterson Family
at the Holidays

As you enjoy
the many gifts
that Christmas
brings your way —
The smiles and joys
and family times
you'll share
this holiday...

Inside Verse:

Please know that you're
remembered
by those who lives
you touch...
And wished a world
of happiness —
because you mean
so much.

TITLE:
Across the Miles
Add-a-Photo
INSIDEVERSE:
Cover Verse:

For You. Dana. From Across the Miles

The Petersons

Inside Verse:

Though nothing ever takes the place
Of greetings spoken face to face.
Still. thoughts must sometimes cross the miles
And take the place of words and smiles...

So. on this Christmas holiday.
This card brings warmest thoughts your way.
Besides a little wish or two
That things are going well for you.

MERRY CHRISTMAS

TITLE: Holy Night
INSIDEVERSE:
Cover Verse:

Somewhere
in the flurry
of the season.
may we find time
to dream
about that blessed
holy night
that changed
the world...

Inside Verse:

Time to give thanks
with all our hearts
that God so loved the world.

Merry Christmas

TITLE: Hope of Christ
INSIDEVERSE:
Cover Verse:

For You.
Dana & Joe

The snow
falls soft
upon the night.
Reflecting
Christmas
joy and light.
The stars
look down
upon the earth.
Remembering
the Christ Child's
birth.

Inside Verse:

May the hope that was born
that silent. holy night
remain in your heart
throughout the year.

Merry Christmas

TITLE: Celebrate the Season
INSIDEVERSE:
Cover Verse:

Happy Holdiays
from the
Smith Family

Inside Verse:

May you celebrate
this beautiful season
with joy in your home.
peace in your world.
and love in your heart!

TITLE: Jolly Santa
INSIDEVERSE:
Cover Verse:

Ho!
Ho!
Ho!

Inside Verse:

You'd be jolly. too.
if you only had to work
one day a year!

Merry Christmas

TITLE: Season's Greetings
INSIDEVERSE:
Cover Verse:

SEASON'S GREETINGS

Inside Verse:

To wish you
all the joys
your heart
can hold!

TITLE:
Happy Holidays
Add-a-Photo
INSIDEVERSE:
Cover Verse:

HAPPY HOLIDAYS

Inside Verse:

Wishing you
all the Season's best.
Michelle.

TITLE: Happy Beginnings
INSIDEVERSE:
Cover Verse:

Happy New Year

Inside Verse:

Hope this is
the happy beginning
of your most
wonderful year yet!

TITLE:
Wish for Peace
Add-a-Photo
INSIDEVERSE:
Cover Verse:

Let peace fill
our hearts
and our homes
until it encircles
our world.

Inside Verse:

Wishing peace and happiness
for you and those you love
through all the days of the new year.

TITLE: Thanksgiving Blessings
INSIDEVERSE:
Cover Verse:

For You. Heather

"Bless friends
and loved ones.
near and far.
with all
the nicest things
there are."

Inside Verse:

Happy Thanksgiving —
and
God bless you
always!

TITLE: Beautiful Day
INSIDEVERSE:
Cover Verse:

Happy
Thanksgiving.
Julie

Inside Verse:

Thinking of you at Thanksgiving
In a warm and affectionate way.
And wishing you all the blessings
Of a beautiful. bountiful day!

TITLE: Thank You
INSIDEVERSE:
Cover Verse:

THANK YOU

Inside Verse:

Just a thank you note from me —
Your gift was perfect as can be!

TITLE: Christmas Trees
INSIDEVERSE:
Envelopes are the first things a recipient sees when getting mail. So it’s worthwhile – and fun – to create. personalize. and print envelopes to go with cards and letters.

Directions:

1. Click on Personalize Your Project to open the Create & Print workspace.
2. Personalize the text. Select the text to write over it or change size. color. and font style.
3. Click Add Page for each additional envelope you want to create.
4. Print your project.

Tips:

Envelopes can be used for mailing stationery. brochures. flyers. notes. greeting cards. and more.

Print your project on scrap paper first to check the alignment. spelling. and overall look of the project.

TITLE: Festive Trees
INSIDEVERSE:
Whether you’re typing. word-processing. or writing longhand. the old-fashioned way. personalized stationery is a nice way to express yourself and impress your correspondent.

You'll need: Paper. 8 1/2 x 11 inches. Use plain white paper. colored paper. or preprinted stationery stock.

Directions:

1. Click on Personalize Your Project to open the Create & Print workspace.
2. Personalize the text. Select the text to write over it or change size. color. and font style.
3. For additional pages. click Add Page and follow the directions.
4. Print your project.

Tips:

Choose a stationery style that fits your mood – whimsical. happy. serious. etc.

Formal stationery traditionally includes the writer’s name and contact information. but don’t feel restricted to that. Specially chosen pictures and quotations can make your stationery uniquely yours.

Many stationery projects have coordinating envelopes. labels. or stickers you can Create & Print as well.

You may want to save your favorite stationery so that you can make more. Click Save and follow the directions.

TITLE: Christmas Card List
INSIDEVERSE:
A decorative Christmas Card List is a must! It’s the perfect way to keep track of all your addresses. and when you sent each holiday card out!

You'll need:

Paper. 8 1/2 x 11 inches.

Directions:


  1. Click on Personalize and Print Your Project to open the Creative workspace.

  2. Personalize the text. Select the text to write over it or change size. color. and font style.

  3. For additional list pages. click Add Page and follow the directions.

  4. Click Print Project to send finished Christmas card list to the printer.

Tips:

Print your project on scrap paper first to check the alignment. spelling. and overall look of the project.
